              One way to visualize it is to think of the particle you want to observe as a croquet ball in motion, and the only way you can "observe" the ball is to whack it with your croquet mallet.  Your very observation changes what you see.<BR><BR>Perhaps now is a good time to post the link to the <A HREF="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DfPeprQ7oGc" TARGET=_blank>What the bleep</A> video that talks about this same thing.  Entertaining, informative, and more than a little bit creepy.

              

              
              
