            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Imagine that you want to measure the frequency of photon at a certain time or point.<BR><BR>Frequency is a function of amplitude over time. <BR><BR>To measure the frequency accurately you will need to measure it over a certain time, which is likely to mean a certain displacement as well. <BR><BR>So you can get a more accurate frequency but the position and time is now more inaccurate.

              

              
              
